sec.p:
To determine if the number of persistent non-synonymous SNPs (nsSNPs) occurring in conjunction with changes in MIC was greater than expected, we developed a simple model to simulate the occurrence of nsSNPs outside of LOH regions at each time point. For each time point (i), a random variable Xi ∼ Pois(λi) was assigned, where λi represents the Poisson parameter for each time point:
λi = m/T × ti;
m = 1471, the number of ORFs with persistent nsSNP;
T = 23, the number of time points;
ti = the length of time (days) for time point (i) divided by the mean length of time.
